Business Brief -- Equimark Corp.:
   Shareholders Agree to Triple
   Authorized Common Shares
Shareholders also agreed to a rights offering, which gives
each holder the right to buy, for $2 a share, 1.25 additional
shares for each share held as of this past Friday.
   Equimark has entered into an agreement with the Tisch
family, which has agreed to buy, under certain conditions all
remaining shares, up to a 24.9% stake, that aren't exercised
by the Feb. 10 expiration date. The Tisch family beneficially
owns about 6.3% of the company's common stock outstanding.